        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 12
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> Kazavon's captain of the guard — a skeleton warrior even before the castle fell, restored by the curse as an anchor and ordered by Mithrodar <strong>never to leave the gatehouse loft (D1)</strong> or its parapets, with two greater shadows (his old bodyguards) in the box-clutter dark. <strong>The bloodless way:</strong> his <strong>golden circlet</strong> (~250 gp) sits in an alcove of Kazavon's tower (D14); its wearer can see through Castothrane's eyes. If a PC carries or wears it he points and rasps, 'Mine... you have what is mine...' — refused, he attacks that character <em>to the exclusion of all others</em> (and if that PC falls, keeps searching the body, ignoring everyone). <strong>Handed the circlet, he sighs, sets it on his skull — and both crumble to dust:</strong> the anchor severed without a blow (his spirit is reabsorbed by the castle; the circlet is lost with him).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
